1. Create a file
touch file.txt
Creates an empty file.

ğŸ“Œ 2. Create a directory
mkdir project
Creates a folder named project.

ğŸ“Œ 3. Create nested directories
mkdir -p dev/app/config
-p creates parent folders if not present.

ğŸ“Œ 4. List files
ls
ls -l
ls -la
-l: long view
-a: show hidden files

ğŸ“Œ 5. View file content
cat file.txt
Prints complete file.

ğŸ“Œ 6. View content page by page
less file.txt
Useful for long files.

ğŸ“Œ 7. Edit file (CLI editor)
nano file.txt
Simple text editor.

ğŸ“Œ 8. Copy file
cp file.txt backup.txt

ğŸ“Œ 9. Copy directory
cp -r project/ project_backup/
-r = recursive (copy folders).

ğŸ“Œ 10. Move or rename
mv file.txt newname.txt
mv file.txt /tmp/

ğŸ“Œ 11. Delete files
rm file.txt

ğŸ“Œ 12. Delete directory
rm -r project/
Or safe delete:
rm -ri project/
-i: asks before deleting.

ğŸ“Œ 13. Find a file
find . -name "file.txt"

ğŸ“Œ 14. Search text inside a file
grep "error" logfile.txt

ğŸ“Œ 15. Check file permissions
ls -l file.txt

ğŸ“Œ 16. Change permissions
chmod 644 file.txt
chmod +x script.sh

ğŸ“Œ 17. Change ownership
sudo chown user:user file.txt

ğŸ”µ 2. Real-Time Scenarios (with practical commands)
Scenario 1: Create a project structure

You want to create a folder structure for a DevOps project:

mkdir -p devops/{ansible,terraform,kubernetes,scripts}
Creates all folders at once.

Scenario 2: Backup configuration files
cp /etc/ssh/sshd_config sshd_config.bak
Takes a quick backup.

Scenario 3: Find all log files larger than 100 MB
find /var/log -type f -size +100M

Scenario 4: Fix error by changing script permission
Script not running?
bash: ./deploy.sh: Permission denied


Fix:
chmod +x deploy.sh

Scenario 5: Clean old logs
rm -rf /var/log/*.gz

Scenario 6: Move all YAML files to a folder
mv *.yaml configs/

Scenario 7: Debug a microservice log in real-time
tail -f app.log

Scenario 8: Search for errors inside a log file
grep -i "error" app.log

